<h2>EverQuestLive.com Redesign Sneak Peak</h2>
<DIV align=center>
<TABLE cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="85%" border=0>
<TBODY>
<TR>
<TD>
<P><B><A href="/lowsrc/community/images/hammerfel/eqlive.jpg"><IMG height=400 hspace=5 src="/community/images/hammerfel/eqlive_tn.jpg" width=195 align=right vspace=5 border=1></A></B></P>
<P>Next week we'll be deploying a redesigned EverQuestLive.com. As most EQ players know, EverQuestLive.com is our Community site for current EverQuest players, while EverQuest.com is our site for newcomers who are interested in learning what this EQ stuff is all about.</P>
<P>We decided to redesign EverQuestLive.com in an effort to better organize and display the immense amount of information we have in a simpler, easier to navigate fashion. To the right is a preview of the design that will appear next week. (Text and feature images are placeholder only.)</P>
<P>Features include:</P>
<P><B>An expanding left menu<BR></B>All the menu items marked with a triangle have sub-sections. Clicking on the triangle will expand that section. <BR>- Clicking the Section name will bring you to the main page for that section and expand the menu.<BR><STRONG>- </STRONG>The menu will remember its state, even for your next visit, so you can leave open the sections you use frequently, while the others remain collapsed.</P>
<P><B>Links </B><BR><STRONG>- </STRONG>A new page under our Community section, with links to the most popular EQ News sites, Class communities, and the player-run Server Communities</P>
<P><B>Featured area</B><BR><STRONG>- </STRONG>Along the top of the front page, we have three sections for features. This allows us to draw special attention to certain items.</P>
<P><B>Three separate news blocks</B><BR><B>- Headlines</B> - These are your official EverQuest news items.<BR><B>- Community</B> - Here is where we will report on what's happening in the EverQuest Community.<BR><B>- Tech Support</B> - This is where news of a more technical nature will be posted. This section will also be redisplayed at the top of the main Support page.</P>
<P><B>Phat Lewt</B><BR><STRONG>- </STRONG>This section will display three EQ items from the Station.com Store.</P>
<P><B>Server Status</B><BR><STRONG>- </STRONG>Our now familiar Server Status area</P>
<P>Every page of the new EverQuestLive.com site is editable through an easy-to-use content management system. This allows us to separate the content from the HTML, and allows for frequent updates from a variety of people at SOE. Now that we have such a solid base to work from, we plan quite a few new features and quite a bit more content for this site. As we near completion on the new features and content, I'll let you know on this page.</P>
<P><BR>Nathan "Hammerfel" Pearce<BR>Director of Web Presence<BR>Sony Online Entertainment</P></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></DIV>



